I once had this hallucination when I was kid, that i still remember 
vividly. Its not that scary now, but it terrified me as a kid. One night, I 
was sitting in my bed at night, and was playing with a stuffed animal. I 
was supposed to be sleeping, so the lights were off. In my room, I had a 
shelf where I kept all of my toys, and that night I looked at it and saw 
Peter Pan's shadow on my wall, grabbing at my toys. I was so petrified that 
I just sat and stared. Then the shadow noticed me and started moving along 
the wall towards me. I screamed and tried to move but I couldn't. Then my 
mother came in and turned on the light, and everything was normal. My 
mother said that I was probably dreaming, but I swear I was awake.﻿

+SaborTheCatHD Absolutely, and it's a really awful condition.

Actually, the origin of the word "nightmare" can be traced to sleep 
paralysis; it comes from a German folktale of a duchess that was "visited 
in the night and sat on" by some sort of demon horse, hence "nightmare". 
The encounter was most likely a case of sleep-paralysis.

But some people experience far scarier things than horses. The most 
frightening case I've heard of is a guy who sometimes see's people with no 
legs crawling towards him and then they disappear when he regains control.

But don't worry, it affects very few people and even if you experience it 
during the night when you wake up you probably wouldn't remember it by 
morning.

top_comment.text:
Gosh I had a lot of nightmares and... ghostly encounters when I was a 
little kid... (*warning, a book will appear on your screen if you 'Read 
more'*)

I had a reoccurring dream about watching TV at night with my parents. We 
were all on the couch, me in the middle. There was a long hallway right 
behind the couch; all the lights were off so it was really dark. I got this 
creepy feeling that something was sneaking up behind us down the hallway, 
so I looked back and I saw the shadow of this dwarve-looking figure like 3 
feet tall, limping down the hallway towards me. I screamed, and told my 
parents there was a monster coming to kill us. I looked at them. Both of 
them looked at me at the same time, and their eyes were completely gouged 
out, just large black holes. They said, "There is no such thing as 
monsters, my dear."

When I was a baby my father told me that he saw someone enter my bedroom in 
the corner of his eye sometimes. He said it was like a "white shadow." 
Recently he got an old red office chair that some people were going to 
throw away. It was similar to the one my grandfather sat in when he told 
stories to my dad; my grandfather died a month before I was born in 1998, 
and my parents said that he really wanted to see me before he died. So 
yeah... we had this red chair just sitting in our living room. A few weeks 
later, I felt like I was being watched. On some days my father said that he 
now had seen a "black shadow" enter my room at night, and he felt his hair 
stand on end. One day during a weeknight my dad was on the computer in the 
living room and I was watching TV in the same room with him. I heard him 
call me to the computer, so I came over and said, "Whatcha want?" My father 
looked at me all confused, and then he said, "I didn't say anything." 
Funny, we both got goosebumps and for a split second we saw the shadow of 
an old man sitting in the chair before it vanished.

One morning I was waiting for the bus in 6th grade. Ya know... just a 
normal, boring morning. I got a chill which was weird because it really 
wasn't that cold out. So I just looked back, and this'll sound really weird 
but, I saw a purple shade in the form of my grandmother. (at the time it 
was my favorite color) She was walking back and forth on my porch like she 
was worried. (She always wore a Phillipino floral dress around her house 
when I visited her with my mom. She was wearing that same dress, and still 
wore it before she died). She looked at me, waved, and then she poofed. 
Before this all happened, she passed away a few months ago from pancreatic 
cancer. At the time that I saw her, we had her ashes in an urn in my house 
for a time before we gave it to one of our other family members. It was 
like a final farewell because she let herself go to rest when my parents 
and I weren't around to say goodbye...
This is where I stop because I already probably buried more than half the 
comments here with mine. O.o *I tolds ya*﻿

comments.text:
+TheIndieGamesNL It may be that you have a genetic predisposition towards 
schizotypal experiences, though that does not mean you necessarily end up  
developing actual schizophrenia; there are multiple symptoms that go 
together  for a diagnosis to be made, but each symptom can also appear 
singularly without any further developments, and oftentimes it can also go 
away again either on it's own or by focusing on understanding what you are 
experiencing and trying to relate to what meaning it might have to you; In 
the case of seeing portals and demons, I would consider it as a  possible 
sign of fears relating to becoming lost, and either fears of other people 
behaving  badly or fears of adopting bad behaviours yourself.

However,  sometimes fantasy is just fantasy, it doesn't have to have any 
further meaning :)

comments.text:
+paddymoep I don't think you're understanding what I say. I don't mean 
people directly get inspired by nature. Whether they do or not is 
irrelevant. I mean that they're influenced by it whether they mean to or 
not. What I meant in my example about humans on an aliens planet is like if 
there were no birds there, or if all the animals had no teeth but rather 
say, suction cup-like parts to tear or kill their food. Rather than 
developing spears humans would likely develop something suction cup like as 
well, even if a spear would work just the same. The art of that 
civilization when depicting mythological beasts from other dimensions would 
likely not have teeth protruding but those suction cups doing whatever they 
do. With no birds or any flying creatures, they would likely need to study 
physics for much longer before they realized the concept of flying. That's 
what I mean when I say they derive it from nature. They do whether they 
want to or not.

In the same light, children born in this environment would eventually have 
their brains adapted to thinking about this type of stuff. People hang 
themselves because they know it will probably work, due to how nature is. 
Vines aren't the only think that can kill you. If hanging had no effect 
whatsoever, then nobody would think of hanging as disturbing at all. If 
touching metal would cause instant death, and hanging nothing, then people 
would think of that as an iconic suicide.

I never said children automatically think grim thoughts. They can, and when 
they do it's very likely to be in an environment that resembled one where 
they were likely to be killed in our hunter gatherer days.

top_comment.text:
This might not be the best video to post this on, but I'm wondering if this 
happens to anyone else.

When you're sleeping and close to waking up, you sometimes hear noises just 
before you wake up. After you get out of bed you realize that the noises in 
your dreams were actually noises happening around your house.

Here's an example. You have a dream about being in a car crash. It ends 
with a crash and you wake up exactly as the crashing noise happens. Then it 
turns out your Mom dropped a plate or something.

The weird part about this is that, while asleep, you have no idea when on 
IF the noise is going to happen yet it syncs perfectly in your dream. It's 
like you know that it's going to happen before it does.

I imagine that after waking up your brain connects the noises to the 
memories from the dream and makes them fit. Still, does anyone else get 
this?﻿
top_comment.author: Dylan W (Thaane)

comments.text:
Dreams are thoughts on the most basic level, and our thoughts happen 
quickly. I think it's possible that our minds only seem to sync things up, 
because we can fill in the blanks pretty much as the sound is happening. 
Our perception of time in regards to dreams is usually way off. What seems 
like minutes or hours in a dream are actually only seconds.
comments.author: Shirley Jones

comments.text:
+Luke F.   I  have dreams that are auditory as well as visual all the time, 
and it's not ambient noise. It can't be because I sleep with the best 
earplugs you can buy to block out noise.. Haven't you ever had a dream that 
you were talking with somebody? Even though it all comes from my brain I 
have no idea or control over what they say. At least on the surface level 
of the dream but who knows what it means psychologically?. Sometimes 
conversations in dreams make perfect sense and sometimes it's silly or 
humorous. I've come up with good ideas during dreams but if I don't wake up 
while I'm still in the dream, I won't remember them. For some reason my 
dreams usually center around either solving some type of puzzle or finding 
my way out of someplace. Lately I've been dreaming about running through 
tunnels, trying to escape an underground prison with 10 or 15 other guys.

top_comment.text:
When I was a little kid I had a shit ton of nightmares.
I remember that it must have been somewhere around my 3rd or 4th birthday, 
I had a dream where I stood in the living room, my mum was like "it's your 
birthday today" and then I went upstairs, only to find my grandma and my 
uncle turn into skeletons. By the time I was 6 they both died of cancer.

I had a very realistic nightmare that I was sleeping in bed with my mum, 
and ghosts just flew around the room. Everything looked as it looks at 
night, I tried to wake my mum but she didn't wake up.

But the absolute worst one of all was that I stood in a room downstairs, a 
room which joined the hallway, living room, and the stairs. Everything was 
dark, except there was someone somewhere in the front in the hallway. A 
light was turned on over there then, but the room I was in was dark. There 
stood a dark figure, which looked the size of maybe an 11 year old boy (I 
was 3 - 6 then). He looked very demonic though. When he looked at me for a 
couple of seconds, everything turned into a gameshow like room, where I was 
looking from above at a TV presenter on the left, my dad in the middle and 
myself on the right. They talked and laughed and suddenly the ground opened 
beneath me and I watched myself fall.
This dream kept recurring for a couple of years, after a couple times I 
knew what's coming next and I wasn't surprised, I knew I was dreaming but 
couldn't wake up. Somehow I couldn't make anything stop. Until one day I 
just looked back at that demon and he looked a bit annoyed, cause he knew I 
wasn't frightened anymore. I woke up then. No gameshow.
But then when I was 10 - 12 that dream recurred again. The demon looked at 
me like he did when I was 3, but I just laughed in his face and was like 
"what you gonna do". He turned his face and walked away and I walked in the 
direction of the living room. Woke up. No gameshow either of course.
He didn't come back since.﻿

My friend and I were babysitting this 4 year old girl. She was just 
playing, and I started painting her nails. Then she said "I used to could 
paint my nails really well." And I stopped and said, "you'll paint them 
really pretty on your own someday." She said, "well I was 16 when I died." 
I was taken aback and responded, "how did you die? You are only 4." She 
said, "I used to be 16. I was murdered by my boyfriend. We were at a cabin, 
and he took me out to the peir. We started fighting and he was yelling at 
me. I didn't know how to swim, and he pushed me in the water. I died that 
day. I was 16." 
My friend and I were so creeped out. All the sudden she forgot was she was 
talking about and wanted us to go play..... she forgot telling us any of 
that. What was weird was her voice was serious, and she spoke in complete 
sentences.

She is 12 years old now. She still doesn't remember saying any of it, but 
she knows about it because we told her. She'll still walk up to me and say, 
"I still have nightmares over that. I can't believe I said those things." ﻿

When I was about four, I had a nightmare about this rocking horse in my 
room named Blaze. I was always terrified of Blaze as a kid (now I put hats 
on him and such, because he is now much smaller than me and I could kick 
his plastic ass). One night, I had a dream that was to this day the most 
vivid dream that I've ever had. No breaks- I had thought that I had just 
woken up in the middle of the night, which was normal for me. I saw Blaze 
just ever so slightly illuminated by the light of the moon, as if he was a 
shadow (shadows seem to be common themes for nightmares). I was petrified. 
Somehow, I knew that I shouldn't move. I kept my breath steady, and tried 
to go back to sleep. I couldn't close my eyes for the longest while. When I 
finally did, I stayed still as stone. After a few minutes, I twitched, ever 
so slightly. My eyes flung open, just in time to see Blaze come to life, 
and silently springing at me, mouth open, and then darkness. 

It's funny. because when I woke up, I just kind of thought, "I KNEW that 
bastard was up to something," and I had to risk getting eaten again to call 
my parents. But I dunno, now the dream is kind of funny. Silly four year 
old me, horses don't fucking eat people. The dream felt so real... I felt 
the sheets and I felt my breathing... creepy as hell. ;-;﻿

sort of pure, blindingly white infinite room that was only me and i was 
there walking around looking for stuff for a good hour. Then i started

started off as a whisper and it got progressively louder as time went by.

all the time. To this day I can remember the demonic figures in the dreams, 
the monsters, the people, the things that would happen. Alot of people 
would blame it on the house we lived in. The house was definitely haunted 
and you can throw all your mythbuster bullshit at me you want but things 
happened in that house that are scientifically impossible. Every person who 
stayed a night at our house would claim they felt like they were being 
watched while they tried to sleep or that there was someone in the 
darkness, and they always had nightmares. When my mother was praying once 
with my auntie, the light bulb in the room literally exploded into a powder 
so fine that you could hold it in your hands. Game disks in our computer 
would also explode into small shards with a huge bang and happened quite 
frequently and that was proven to be impossible on mythbusters. All the 
dishes in the house were somehow taken out from the cupboards and layed on 
the floor when my mother went to the bathroom. Tell me ghosts and spirits 
aren't real all you want but you aren't arguing that shit with me.﻿

top_comment.text:
One day back in the 90's, my mum (16) was babysitting my uncle (5) he was 
just messing around with some toys but as mum turned around, in the doorway 
there was a man, just a regular man standing in the doorway to the living 
room they were both in. my mum backed up to the far opposite corner of the 
room away from the man (obviously) but he disappeared as she turned around. 
No sound was heard when he left. My mum checked all the doors, windows any 
entries into the house were all shut tight. As my mum entered the room my 
uncle was in he said " so you saw the man too" As my grandmother came home 
(mum of my mum) she was told of what happened and about the man,she was 
terrified. She washed my uncles hair everyday, as she did this he talked to 
"the man" who he said was standing behind my grandmother when she cleaned 
his hair (obviously there was nothing there) she just assumed it was an 
imaginary friend of my uncle. I was not born during those times but anyone 
who does not believe in ghosts just because there is no proof of them in a 
video does not mean they do not exist. I have never seen a ghost before but 
I believe my mums word over any other. its 2014 and my uncle (22) was in 
his home and he heard a familiar voice call his name. ﻿

I remember I was staying at my sisters house for a couple weeks and they 
had a spare room for me with a computer set up! any way I was playing 
minecraft at about 12:30 am when my niece (whose bedroom was next to mine) 
Opened the door to my room stared at me and said "He doesn't like us being 
here... This is his home... not ours..." then straight after she walked 
back to bed. I followed her back to her room but it seemed like she was 
fast asleep (I thought she was faking) so I said to her "you shouldn't be 
up this late" but she didnt respond so I shook her and she woke up all 
groggy and asked me why I woke her up! I told her what she just did and she 
just stared at me and told me that it wasn't her... I left the room annoyed

top_comment.text:
Well, I guess I'll give my story then: Not too long ago I got a new mobile 
phone that was used and when I opened it up, I did notice that there was 
still some messages, contacts and what-not left on the phone. Personally I 
did find it weird as I just thought it was normal for people to delete all 
of their contacts and what-not after using it and selling (It was a fairly 
new phone too) so it caught me by surprise that the contacts were still 
here.

The first day or so was perfectly fine, but then I suddenly got a phone 
call from a number I don't recognise and as soon as I answered it, I said 
'Hello?' and I was waiting for the other person to talk back and it sounded 
like a man was lightly breathing in the phone but then the douche bag 
decided to hang up on me. I just thought to myself 'Well, fuck you too 
then.' and I just shrugged it off as a prank call. But the next day, the 
same call came in again and I answered it, the same thing happened - light 
breathing and then hung up.

This continued one again the next day and I answered with a really impolite 
'What?' and the same shit happened again. It pissed me off so I just 
blocked the number on my phone and decided to ignore the call entirely. For 
the next few days, the number would keep trying to call (By telling me I 
missed the calls but my ringtone never want off) and I was thinking to 
myself 'Hah, serves you right for being an asshole.' But then not long 
after I blocked the number, the exact same number somehow managed to get 
the number to my second phone (I have two :I) which actually creeped me out 
quite a bit and I thought to myself 'How in the world did you get this 
number?' and I just blocked it again on my second phone. For the next few 
days, I kept on getting missed call notifications on my phones from the 
exact same number and at least then it felt like I had that little bit of 
peace.

The calls stopped for a while, about roughly a week or two but then for 
some unknown reason, the call came in - my ringtone went off and the phone 
vibrated despite the fact that the same number was blocked so I decided to 
pick up the phone and given them a bit of badmouthing, something amongst 
the lines of 'Look, I'm getting really tired of your shit, what the hell do 
you want?' But I noticed that just before it hung up once again that there 
were voices speaking in the background of a man and a woman in a language 
that I seriously couldn't discern, it didn't feel like gibberish because it 
certainly felt like a a conversation between the two voices but I couldn't 
make out what language it was, along with heavier breathing than before 
which really got under my skin. This genuinely creeped me the fuck out and 
I made the effort to block the number however way I can, as well as 
blocking any calls that aren't in my contacts list.

There were no calls from that number until about another 2 or 3 weeks later 
and this is where it got really, really creepy. Once again, my phone 
somehow ignored the blocking as if the number was already in my contacts 
list which it wasn't and I just got really pissed off that I just answered 
the phone and I shouted down the phone with something like 'What the fuck 
do you want you fucking asshole!? Don't you have anything better to do with 
your fucking time!?' but as soon as I said what needed to be said, this 
call felt really, really off as I noticed the sounds were completely 
different this time which was a really deep base-like grumbling moan that 
was quiet but noticeable along with the sounds of what seemed to be like a 
heart beat and very ominous squishing noises, sort of like when tearing 
meat from the bones of a chicken but very, very slowly, it didn't sound too 
healthy. But very soon after that grumbling moan began to change pitch and 
tone almost as if it was someone or something trying to speak through the 
phone. The difference here is that it was in English but it was hard to 
make out everything it was actually saying, but what I did pick up on the 
call was 'When the red star ignites the world, we will be one with the dust 
in the darkest skies. They have decided.' and I immediately just hung up 
and I blocked the number whichever way I can and to my own surprise, that 
number has never tried to call me ever again but I know I'm going to 
remember that phone call for a while.

I did a bit of research on the number and it sounded like a lot of people 
were having 'prank call' experiences with this number ranging from 
breathing to static to gibberish voices, as well as actual people asking 
some very ominous questions such as full bank details, asking young girls 
if they want to go for a model shoot and calls from 'lonely' people, the 
stories I've heard from this phone number is quite creepy but nobody else 
seemed to have experienced the exact same thing as me, albeit some of the 
stories I have heard from others were also really creepy but it didn't 
match my story which I found very odd and strange. The number is real and 
it exists today so if you really want to know what the number is, it's 
this: +441332387210 - apparently it belongs to a company called 'Dream 
Money' and they have been harassing people for what seems to be something 
like 8 years now and as the years went on and on, the calls became much, 
much creepier - so reading that up, I found it evident with the call I had. 
I do believe it might be simply prank calling but I do get this really odd 
feeling after having to hear what I did. I don't know, I would love to know 
if anyone else has ever had any strange calls from this number or any other 
theories about the call?﻿

top_comment.text:
Well I have a story ( I'm an Atheist so I'm not some religious nutter and I 
generally consider myself more of a "give me evidence and I will believe 
you" kind of guy) it isn't as "scary" as the other stories here but it is 
just as bad imo, well When I was in grade 8 (6 years ago) my grandma passed 
away, at the time my Dad was working furiously and had no time to go and 
scatter the ashes at the place my Grandpa was scattered ( a place known 
here in Australia as wivenhoe dam) anyway he put the ashes in the 
downstairs computer room and must have left them there for a total of a 
month, the first two weeks were all good but the third I started to "feel" 
things while I was laying in bed, at first I just brushed it off as a 
little wind or a puffy blanket molding around my legs while the air seeps 
out through the gaps and deflates but then it got worse... I started 
feeling STRONG grabs and clearly hand feels around my legs, tough strong 
grabs that even though I didn't want to admit what I felt I knew deep down 
that was a human hand, it kept happening and the grabs got stronger and 
stronger and then she started tugging on me and pulling blankets off it was 
seriously hell I mean I was TERRIFIED, I told my dad "I don't care what you 
do with her just fucking get rid of the ashes" he FINALLY dumped the ashes 
after my mum told him to get them the hell out of the house, not one single

Since people are sharing their stories, I might as well too.

Recently, I've been having some odd continuities within my dreams. The 
first part of it has to do with this temple/fortress-like structure. Out in 
the middle of the desert, there's this pyramid, but it's somewhat different 
from the usual Egyptian pyramid representation. Imagine a normal pyramid, 
but with castle-like walls around it, nearly blocking the view of the 
pyramid itself. The spires are square-shaped, and there are no conical 
roofs. There is no entrance to within the walls either. How I got inside in 
the first place is beyond me. Inside the spires, was a singular cylindrical 
room with a door going to within each wall, and to the next spire. The 
rooms and halls were completely empty too. After cycling through the walls 
and spires, I eventually came into this large rectangular room. In the 
center, a purplish orb with a black core. I touched it, it came close to my 
face, it became all I saw, and the dream ended.

Later on, I kept having dreams end with me coming near a similar orb, but 
with something different about it each time. One time, it had these objects 
around it that made it look like an eye; another time having a sort of 
flame come off of it, but it went out in all directions; the most recent 
iteration having thin, whip-like tendrils thrashing about.

Also, they tended to be on a pedestal, presented at the top of some sort of 
stairwell.

I don't know if it means anything, and I'm sure this sounds like bullshit, 
but remember; 'twas but a series of dreams.﻿

Once, me and a few friend at around the age of 12 went camping up in the 
Blue Ridge mountains of SC, in a cabin. the bathroom was about 50 feet down 
a path, and it was a cement building with a streetlight-esque light outside

perfectly still, on the stone floor. i then climbed back to the bunk, and 
fell back to sleep. my friends awoke in horror, when they saw a mini 
waterfall of blood coming off the edge of my bunk. i dont remember much 
after that, other than half the skin from my right foot missing. ﻿

Look into these first consult a naturopath doc should be 1800 numbers or 
research yourself using your own judgement if your on meds or if you have 
other conditions ie. ulcers etc.  If it is cancer there are a few things 
you can try that are not too expensive. Stop eating refined sugar or any 
kind of sugar if you can. artificial sweetners are even worse. 
Unpasteurized honey is the best alternative.  One person commented 
cannabis, if that is something you want to try, look up infusing oil or 
juicing fresh buds if you have access to cannabis. There is also 
oxygenation therapy. Using baking soda or FOOD GRADE hydrogen peroxide( has 
to be food grade is different then the drug store stuff for scrapes and 
stuff). Eissac tea you could look into as well. All are cheap except the 
cannabis option depending on its accessibility in your area.  Hope things 
work out for you.

This is creepy... I grew up in a haunted house, so I have experienced a 
bunch of things. Some really scary things, and some  things that weren't 
scary at all. However, I am certain that I have had visits from my deceased 
relatives, especially my grandmother, more than once.

Once evening, I had made myself some tea and a couple sandwiches. As I 
walked towards the living room, a shut door suddenly opened. My fiancée was 
in the living room and nobody else was there. I suddenly felt a presence 
and the urge to speak Polish, which I did and asked if and who was there. 
The door closed, carefully and I felt an ice cold hand om my shoulder and a 
whispering voice which was familiar; it was my grandmother. However, I 
couldn't really hear what she said... but after that, I could clearly see a 
picture of her in my head, and the she disappeared.


I was born and raised in Sweden, so I (obviously) speak both Swedish and 
English... but my Polish is not really fluent - but at the time it was 
nearly perfect. That schocked me.﻿

+Emster Erick
The spirit I faced was not demonic. It was strong and VERY angry and evil,  
but not even near as strong as a demonic presence. This particular spirit 
had been following my fiancée since she was an orphan.

The night this happened, I woke up and noticed how unnaturally dark it was. 
Sure, it was in the middle of the winter, but the darkness was too 
extreme... you could almost feel it. I looked at the bedroom door and felt 
a pair of eyes gazing right into my eyes through the door and my first 
thought WAS "demon".

I tried to was my fiancée up, but no matted how hard I tried, nothing 
happened; she wouldn't wake up.

I have a crucifix on the bedroom wall, so I looked at it, made the sign of 
the cross, and said a short, but powerful, prayer and said out loud "well, 
if that's the way you want it..."

I started massing and praying and making demands that this evil entity 
would leave us alone. It got even angried, as the door to the bedroom 
started to rattle violently, but it couldn't enter the room. Even the 
neighbors asked the following day about a rattling sound coming from our 
apartment.

As it got angrier, the door rattled even more violently. At this point, I 
invoked the archangels and saints to pray for us and our protection. Now, 
the rattling wasn't as strong anymore... and I kept on going, never 
lowering my guard. After around 45 minutes, it was driven away and nothing 
has ever disturbed us since.

My fiancée even mentioned the following day how calm and quiet everything 
seemed at home.

comments.text:
A really creepy thing happened to me too when I was a kid. Right next to my 
house on the other side of the street there is a small little house - 
nobody lived there for decades. So all my childhood, that house was place 
that scared me, even if nothing actually happened there until that day and 
nothing after... it wasnt scary house, probably it feelt just creppy for 
the fact that nobody lived there, there was no light, and it was full of 
trees and vegetation... In perioud on my street there were ditches, for 
water pipes... we had them the entire summer until the pipes where put in 
and burried. So we played a lot in them. One day we played hide and seek 
(or something like that), and I was with my brother in the ditch (it was 
around 20:00 o'clock, i know this because of the sun light), and walking in 
the ditch we found ourselfs right before the small house... There I saw it, 
I dont remeber very well the details, but it was a tall (around 2 m) white 
silhouette right next to the house, it feelt feminine and it seemed to wear 
a dress, so in my memories I use to recall it as ''the bride''.The first 
thing I did was to ask my brother if he see it too ? And he confirmed.... I 
dont remeber to be scared, I think that I... we where fascinated, I dont 
really know for how long we stared and how did we leave (and even trough I 
think we said to the other kids about it when we left, I dont remeber to 
mention it before my parents..), all I remeber is that night I watched at 
that house trough my window fascinated by what I saw and wandering if is 
still there. And here is where it get actually creepy: it never let a 
trauma or something, i dont remeber that in the rest of the years of my 
childhood to use the bride as a reason of fear towards the house, I 
continued to fear the house, but like before it was scary because it was an 
unhabited house. The thing is that because of the lack of memories, and the 
fact that the few things I remeber are unclear (even trough I remeber most 
of that day and what we did) I trought it was a dream (that my happy days 
full of adventures in the long ditch combined with a fantasy and resulted 
in that), so I forget everything. Until one day, few years later, I was 
with some friends and we said scary stories, and I remembered that thing I 
saw so in the joke I said to my brother: ''Do you remeber what we saw that 
night at the house ?'' or something like that and he answered: ''The bride 
? Yeah I remeber.'' I was still a child, so I was shocked, but not enaf to 
mean something. And in a weird way I forget that discussion too, until one 
day, in adolescence, when I talked with my father about the subject and the 
perceptions of animal towards ghosts and stuffs, and he mentioned, 
something that happened in my family, after an electrician died, every 
night for a month a white shilouette appeared right in that place... my 
aunt saw it every time and was terified by it, and the dog would bark 
towards that place all the night but wont get closer... So I remebered the 
dream (because this was in my perception), mentioning the event, my brother 
entered in the room and... I dont remeber if he heard the discussion and 
intervened or I asked about it, but I remeber his shocking words: ''Oh, the 
white bride in that evening, I remeber it, we saw it togeder.'' His 
memories about it are the same, the only detail that he remebers better 
than me is, the fact that it was a bald bride _. I never actually had a 
serious discussion with him, just the 2 of us about it, I dont know why, is 
something inside me, like a fear that stops me. But one thing is clear, 
that day we saw something unbelivable, something that should be in our mind 
clear and powerfull, but for some reason, there is like a mist in our 
memories, that make us to forget it, or ignore it, we remeber we saw 
something, and we have an image of what we saw, but any detail or event 
that happened in that time and imediatly after, doesent exist. Since that 
discussion with my father is been like 7 years, and the only new thing I 
could remeber: me staring fascinated at the little house from my window. Is 
like we saw something we shouldnt, and that thing made us keep the 
silence...
 Tomorrow I will talk with my brother about it, I hope I will remeber.
comments.author: David Green

One time i had a dream about my mom going to Florida (I live in Michigan) 
with her law partner because she is a lawyer, and in the dream me and my 
dad were home and I saw that mom left her phone, and that i hadn't heard 
from her in a few days. So, I grabbed her phone, dialed her partners' 
number, and called. But nobody picked up. I tried again, no answer. (They 
also have a secretary, too.) so i tried calling her, too. No answer. But I 
guess I knew the hotel's room number, so I called that, too. NO ANSWER. So 
I got worried. My dad said, "It's okay, try calling back in a few hours." 
So i did. STILL. NO. ANSWER. So I called her parter one last time, and 
someone picked up. (They were on their way to somewhere.) But I swear I 
heard a crash, but a second before, I heard "LOOK OUT! YOU RAN A LIGHT! 
THERES A CAR COMIN-" and then there was a crash, and what sounded like 
metal sliding on the ground. The call ended. I didn't get the chance to say 
I loved her. And my dad said, "What happened?!" "Is she okay?!" And then I 
said, "she died." And then I woke up. And she was there, and I gave her a 
big hug. And started crying. ﻿

that my mom was escorting me and my brothers through a burning building. 
Running around corners as fast as we could, almost being crushed by 
collapsing walls and ceilings. My mom was holding my hand while I was 
holding my other 3 brothers' hands, telling us not to let go.  When we 
finally got outside, she told us to wait here so she can go back to save 
our dad. I started sobbing, pleading with her not to leave us. My brothers 
started to cry and plead as well. She told us she will be back. I kept 
begging her not to go back. She put her hands on my cheeks and told me she 
WILL be back, she promised. She ran back inside and moments later, the 
entire building collapses. I started balling in tears while calling out to 
my mom. Shortly after that, I woke up with my pillow and face blotched with 
sobbing tears almost dried up. I was soooooooooooooooooooooo relieved it 
was all a dream. I have never been so scared in my life. I ran to my mom 
and dad's room and hugged them both while crying, eventually telling them 
what happened.

The first is when I was younger, once in a while I would go to my 
grandparents bedroom at night and stand at the end of the bed and just 
stare...when they asked me what I was doing I would make an angry sounding 
noise and walk back to my room and would not remember it nomatter how many 
times they told me.

The second is in our o;d house (I was aboout 5) I would have these horrible 
nightmares about a figure standing at the end of my bed, it had the body of 
a dog standing on its hind legs and a rotting human head with no eyes. I 
would wake up screaming and my feet would be warm as if someone was 
breathing on them. after I told my grandma about it she seemed worried but 
told me not to worry about it, after awhile it spoke to me...it was a 
hidious, scratchy voice and it told me to come play with it in the basment

i still remember a dream that used to haunt me all the time when i was a 
kid. The dream would start with me, walking down the stairs at night (not 
able to control where i was going) then going into our living room, where 
all the furniture had been removed but one chair (a single seat sofa). The 
chair was not where it used to, (we have connected livingroom and 
"special"diningroom so you can walk through) the chair was facing through 
the dining area (a "long" room, not very wide) then i would sit down in the 
chair, still not able to move myself, and fear growing inside of me (i do 
not know why), then this dark siluette would appear, with a human like 
shape (even though it was kind of shifting shape/waving) i could not see if 
it had a face or anything, it was just darkness. it would just stand in 
front of me, and all hapiness would get dragged out of me, and fear grew. 
the shape came closer and closer, while i still could not move. i would 
close my eyes (in the dream) and i could hear noises (what of i do not 
know, but it was caos) i could not see anything (my eyes were closed) and 
colors flashing would appear and my head banging around, i would take my 
hands on my ears to stop hearing, but nothing worked, it was like it was in 
my brain, controlling it, destroying it, by making me crazy. then i would 
allways wake up crying (A LOT!) feeling really sad. 

This is a dream that i have had uncountable times during my childhood. and 
to this date i do not know anything more frightening than that nightmare (i 
dont know why, i believe since it made me so sad, etc) wonder if this is 
caused by anything or means anything, its just different from anything else 
i have had later. comments are appreciated :)﻿

My grandfather fought in the Pacific in WWII.

One time when I was 5 and my sister was 3, she said "Remember when Grampa 
stabbed the man?".
Neither of us had met Grandpa yet, so I didn't know what she meant. I asked 
her about this mystery man.

"You know.... the man with the gun who shot Grampa's friend on the beach. 
He screamed REALLY loud when Grampa stabbed him! He's still screaming now, 
even though he has no neck!"

A few years later, Grandpa was telling his old war stories to my dad, and I 
eavesdropped in. He told a story that went something like this;

"It was 1942. My buddy and I were shootin' and shootin' the Japs as they 
were runnin' 'cross the front at Guadalcanal. Pickin' 'em off 1 by 1. One 
of the bastards got up next to us, flanked us, an' the bastard filled my 
buddy with bullets. Before he turned and saw me, I charged him, an' stabbed 
him in the throat an' through the jaw with my knife. He dropped his gun 
immediately, and even though I knew I cut his windpipe, he screamed like 
hell for what must've been at least 10 seconds before dropping to the 
ground."﻿

top_comment.text:
When I was a child of four or five, I guess I had an overactive imagination 
like most children did at that age. Anyhow, I had most of the normal fears. 
I had to have my closet closed at night so that I wouldn't see the dark 
shapes of my clothing in the darkness, and I always jumped into bed so that 
nothing could grab me from underneath while the lights were out. However, I 
had one fear that wasn't quite as standard for a child. I had a very 
distinct fear of a man that would stand outside my door at night and wait 
for me to go to sleep. When I closed my eyes, I could see him. A dark 
silhouette of man just standing, still and waiting. It terrified me because 
I didn't know what he wanted to do. Because of my fears I started to lose a 
lot of sleep. I would be up half the night afraid of the man outside my 
door. I would sleep in very late, be exhausted during the day, and always 
beg my parents to let me stay up later because I was afraid of going to 
bed. Eventually it got to the point where I knew that I needed to do 
something about it. My other fears were easily enough solved. I was already 
closing the closet door and turning out the light next to my bed last so I 
didn't have to worry, but the man was different. The monsters under my bed 
and in the closet were the typical kind of imaginary nighttime monsters 
that wanted to jump out and grab you, so merely avoiding them through my 
regular methods was enough to put me at ease. The man was different though. 
He didn't want me to see him. He wanted me to go to sleep without noticing 
him, and that's what made him so terrifying to me.

 I told my parents about the man, and they told me that he wasn't real and 
that I should stop worrying about him, but I couldn't. I kept losing sleep 
and I kept seeing the man when I closed my eyes. One night though, I came 
up with a solution. I left the door open before getting into bed. That may 
seem strange, but I thought it out for a long time before doing it. If I 
left the door open, then I would be able to see out into the hallway to 
make sure that the man wasn't there long enough to get to sleep. It would 
leave me vulnerable once I was asleep, but my parents had told me I was 
just imagining him, so it wouldn't do me any harm once I was asleep. On top 
of that, even if he was real, a closed door with no lock wasn't going to do 
much to stop him from getting to me. With all this in mind, I left the door 
open at night and it worked. I didn't see the man outside my door when I 
closed my eyes anymore, and I stared into the darkness until I fell to 
sleep. A couple of times I thought I saw some movement or shifting in the 
shadows, but as soon as I blinked it was gone, and I chalked it up to the 
same imagination that had dreamed up the man in the first place.

Over time, I forgot all of my fears, but my nighttime routine for dealing 
with them remained the same out of habit. I would always leave my door open 
at night, and I told my parents not to close it because it bothered me. A 
couple of years later, my sister said she saw the back of a dark figure 
looming through hallway when she got up to go to the bathroom. Looking back 
on it, I realize that the bathroom is between my room and hers, but at the 
time I paid her childish ramblings no heed with the man that stood outside 
my door almost entirely forgotten. A year or two after that, my dad said he 
saw a tall dark figure dart into the toy room in the basement. He followed 
it and flicked on the lights to find that nobody was there. The toy room 
has no windows, and only the one door, so there was nowhere for it to go, 
but whoever it was had seemingly vanished into thin air. The story 
interested me, since my dad was never one to tell even the smallest of 
lies, but again I made no connection between it and the man who stood 
outside my door so many years ago.

One day, I was heading off to school when I saw a pale white face watching 
me from the door of my house out of the corner of my eye. I looked back at 
it to see nothing. Dismissing it immediately, I went off to school without 
incident. When I came back home, I started to see the face watching me 
again. Every once in a while I would spy it, but it would disappear 
immediately. I thought that it was just my brain playing tricks on me, 
since the image was already in my head. I payed so little mind to the 
hallucinations that I didn't even tell a single person about them. The only 
real oddity was that I would only see the faces in my house... That was 
until I had one of my friends over. We were sitting in the basement in what 
used to be the toy room. I was looking something up on the computer that 
was now positioned in the room, opposite to the closet. The closet was open 
just a foot or two, and my friend was spinning around on a chair next to 
me, waving his feet absently. This meant that he had a quick glimpse into 
the closet every couple of seconds. After a short while, he jumped off of 
the chair with a screech, and whirled to face the closet. I asked him what 
was wrong and he pointed to the closet, swearing to me that he saw a pale 
white face smiling at him from the closet. At fist I was ready to laugh it 
off as him either playing a prank on me or getting wrapped up in my 
hallucinations, but then I remembered that I hadn't told him about them 
yet, nor anyone else for that matter. It was illogical. There was no way he 
could have hallucinated the same thing as me without at least hearing a 
description of the hallucination first. For the first time in years, I was 
terrified. He went home and I went to bed that night, still trying to make 
sense of the ordeal. Before going to bed, I made a decision that seemed 
minor at the time. I decided, for the first time since I was a toddler, to 
sleep with my door closed. I don't know what it was, but I thought that 
maybe it would offer me a little bit of protection if there really was 
something in my house. After a while, I started to doze off. It was then 
that I heard a loud thump on my door, followed moments later by some 
scratching noises. I flicked on the light next to my bed, thoroughly 
spooked, when I remembered that my family had a dog that would scratch on 
doors when she wanted to be let in to a room. I sighed in relief and was 
deciding whether or not to bother getting up and letting her in when I 
heard another noise. There was a soft click of a door handle being grasped 
firmly, followed by a loud violent rattling. The door handle turned back 
and forth sporadically, jerking and twisting violently for several seconds 
before suddenly stopping and leaving me in deadly silence. I sleep with my 
door closed now.﻿

'memorial'. While my dad was getting something, I sat down and waited. When 
I looked to my left, I saw what appeared to be a Japanese man, wearing what 
seem to be a greenish coat. My dad came back to me. I said do you have your 
drink, and he said yes, but when I looked back over to where the man was 
sitting? GONE. I. Was..Petrified.


My last one is when I was at my cousins house. When me and my 2nd cousin 
were...Roleplaying...We saw a shadow go the speed of a baseball that 
Herrara from KC Royals would throw. We stopped playing and tried out simple 
solutions of what happened. But it happened again. We. Ran. Up. Stairs. 
And. Hid. In. The. KITCHEN. When we came out, the adults we're laughing at 
us and asked us what happened. We literally YELLED at the adults that 
pranking us wasn't funny, but then my 2nd cousin's mother said no one else 
was down there except us two. We didn't believe it. But then, my uncle went 
down, he clearly saw something.


Those are probably my 3 horrible parts of my life.

top_comment.text:
Here's my take on these strang phenomenons. You can agree with me, or 
disagree, I don't really care. But, I believe that many of these strange 
and creepy occurences are, in fact, demons.

Demons do, indeed, roam this planet every day, or so I believe. Regardless 
of belief, everyone knows that demons are evil beings. They may not 
necessarily attack you, or even cause physical harm. Instead, I believe 
that they'd prefer to torment people endlessly.

Now, this has never happened to me, and I certainly pray that it never 
does. But, and as I've explained to my friends who have seen weird things, 
I believe I know what they are, and therefore they do not bother me. I'm 
not the type to be fooled into thinking monsters or ghosts exist.

When visiting my grandmother's house, we passed over a bridge going over a 
river. I said to my mother "I died here" I was about one and a half years 
old, so my mother just assumed I was telling a story, "well, what 
happened"? She asked, I responded with "You weren't my mommy, but Mamaw 
(that's my grandma's nick name) was still my grandma, I was bigger and I 
had red hair" "well how'd you die?" She asked, going along with my story, 
"we fell off of that bridge" I replied "the car tipped over in the water 
and I couldn't breath." Startled by this, my mom looked for a story of a 
young red headed boy drowning in that river, she never told me if she did, 
but I will now use the POWER OF GOOGLE!﻿

captions.text:
• From imaginary friends resembling people
who had died, to an infant that speaks of

a fireplace where dead babies go, we count
15 of the creepiest things little kids have

ever said to parents and babysitters
15 - Braids,

• A person walking around their aunt's house
when they spotted their 4 year old cousin

April sitting on the stairs pulling funny
faces

• When asked, April mentioned she was copying
the lady with the braid, pointing towards

a bean running parallel to the stairs, pulling
invisible faces

• April claimed the invisible woman's braids
were around her neck for some reason, hanging

by her braid
• The funny faces April seemed to be copying

were like someone gasping for air
14 - Joe (matthewo),

• A father who had a best friend named Joe
that committed suicide - Joe's wife called

the father blaming herself for Joe's death
• The dad consoled her and reminded her

that Joe loved her very much and that she
was surely not to blame - he hung up the phone

and checked on his kids who were fast asleep
• He went back downstairs only to come back

up and find his son Matty awake, silently
weeping on the side of his bed

• When the dad asks what's wrong, his son
replies "Rick, it's not her fault. I love

her. It's not her fault" - then rolls back
onto the bed fast asleep

• The father was terrified
13 - Captain,

• A mother to a 7 year old child that claims
her son had an invisible friend known as "The

Captain", an old man with a long beard
• The kid told his mum that the captain

informed him when he grows up, his job will
be to kill people, and that the captain would

tell him exactly who it was that should be
murdered

• The kid cried, saying he didn't want to
kill when he grew up, but that the captain

said he didn't have a choice and, even worse,
he'd get used to all the killing after a while

12 - Dead Babies (PersonMcNugget),
• A man and his wife who bought an old house

in Western Canada, one time renovating their
basement when their friend came around to

visit
• This friend was alone with their 2 year

old son, who was barely old enough to talk
let alone understand what he was saying, when

the kid took his hand and led him over to
the chimney, to which he looked up and said

clearly and fluently, "That's where the dead
babies go"

• There was nobody that would have told
him that, no older kids to say it as a joke

- this 2 year old kid just said it out of
the blue

11 - Dead Cop,
• A person's 4 year old niece who would

blame things she did on an imaginary friend,
as well as watch scooby doo with her

• When asked, the niece explained her mysterious
friend was dead, and that she was a police

officer like her father - first meeting her
when she was inside her mother's belly before

being born
• A few months before that time, a policewoman

named Tracy had been hit by a train in a town
right next to the one she happened to be in

- and before she died, she was heavy into
scooby doo

10 - Previous Life,
• Between the ages of 2 and 6, this one

woman's son would tell her the same story
about how his soul picked her to be his mother

• In a bright room with people lined up
like dolls, a suited man would lead the infant

down the line and pick his own parents
• At an early age, the kid had a fascination

with World War 2 fighter jets, even describing
their individual parts and the region they

were used in
9 - Faceless,

• A person looking after their little cousin
from Montana, one who claims to have an imaginary

friend he could only describe as the "Creeper
Man"

• It lives in his mum and dad's bedroom,
watching their whole family all night long

for whatever reason, but when the kid was
asked about the creeper man he gave a chilling

answer
• When asked what he looks like, the kid

merely mentioned "Oh, he doesn't have a face"
8 - Yellow Eyes (RachelSays),

• A woman with a 3 year old son who would
turn to her and say "Mommy, the very big man

with big yellow eyes is looking at you"
• He then pointed at nothing, laughed and

said "He's hiding now, he will come when you
are sleeping"

• Another night, the kid said, "I'm not
going to be four. I'm going to die, and you

will put me down into the hole - the man told
me, and I will be scared by then you'll die

too and come with me"
• Which is a clear indicator your son is

a spawn of the devil
7 - Staring,

• One babysitter watched a few kids while
their parents were off watching a movie - a

pretty simple thing, they just put them to
bed and spent the whole night watching T.V

• The next day, one of the kids told his
parents something incredibly strange: that

the babysitter had NOT watched T.V all night,
that instead they'd stood in the bedroom doorway

and stared at the kid for a very long time,
smiling

• The babysitter was so confused that they
didn't even know how to respond

6 - Lady on the Roof (aamiina),
• A 3 year old sleeping in her bed when

she started screaming, the mother walked in
to find out what's wrong only to hear her

kid yelling the words "Remove the lady from
the roof" over and over, pointing towards

the corner of the roof
• Not too long after while flicking through

some photos, the mother found a picture of
her own mother who died when she was young

- and when her 3 year old kid saw the photo
she flipped out

• Despite never seeing her grandma before,
she pointed directly at her and said "she

was the lady on the roof"
5 - Mystery Mother (universe_hopper),

• A child with the recurring dream of living
with a different family to their own - vivid

memories of a different mother
• When the child told their actual mother

about the dream, she reveals the day she gave
birth - a mysterious woman was cradling the

baby in her arms, and when she spotted the
mother, she put the baby down and ran off

• The description of this woman lined up
with the kid's description of the mother from

their dream, and both of them had always felt
like they belonged to different families - as

if their souls had been mixed up
4 - Premonitions,

• This one kid who sleep walked every night,
turning off all the electronics in the house,

grabbing all the kitchen knives, aligned them
in a circle, sat in the middle and talked

gibberish
• When their dad tried to get them out of

the circle, the kid would pick up a knife
and shout "He will get you" until he backed

away, then continue to sit there for 30 minutes
• The next day when asked about what happened,

the kid spoke of a nightmare about this man
dressed in all black with fire red light behind

him, speaking of awful things and how it was
him doing it

3 - Chop (joysprite),
• A mother with a 3 year old daughter who

turned around one day to say "Don't you remember,
Mommy? Before, when you were the daughter

and I was the mother, they came and chopped
all our heads off. Chop, chop, the whole village."

• Even though the mother was taken aback
and a little shocked, she tried to wave it

off saying "Fortunately I don't remember the
head chopping"

• To which her daughter chimed in, "Well
it happened and I remember it really well"

making vicious chopping motions with her hands
2 - Jack in Hell (spnoelle),

• A kid's stepfather named Jack who sexually
molested his mother when she was young, excluded

from her family's life when she got older
• The kid didn't know any of this, and Jack

died with the mother getting informed by telephone
that day - the kid walked into the living

room to say "He's screaming in my room and
won't stop."

• When she asked who was screaming, the
kid said the name Jack, and that he won't

stop screaming that he's in hell
• She asked her kid to describe this Jack,

which they did - even down to the hospital
gown Jack wore when he died

1 - Dream Bullets (sheldon711)
• The author's 6 year old cousin who lost

their grandfather to a robbery at the convenience
store he ran when the armed robber pulled

out a gun and shot him
• To lessen the blow, the cousin's mother

told her that grandpa had passed away in his
sleep and that he was in heaven now

• To which the little girl replied, "Are
you sure he wasn't shot?", which her mother

denied, and the girl explained "Because I
heard gunshots in my dream last night"

title: 15 Creepiest Things A Child Has Ever Said
